import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import networkx as nx
from matplotlib.lines import Line2D

# Define the graph
G = nx.DiGraph()

# Define categories and their colors
categories = {
    "Senolytics": "green",
    "Senomorphics": "yellow",
    "Senoblockers": "red",
    "Senoreversers": "purple",
    "Senotherapeutics": "blue"
}

# Add the central node
G.add_node("Senotherapeutics", size=6000, color=categories["Senotherapeutics"], subset="center")

# Define drugs and their mechanisms of action
drugs = {

# Add nodes and edges for each category
for category, color in categories.items():
    if category != "Senotherapeutics":
        G.add_node(category, size=3000, color=color, subset="category")
        G.add_edge("Senotherapeutics", category)

        for drug in drugs.get(category, []):
            G.add_node(drug["name"], size=1000, color=color, subset=category)
            G.add_edge(category, drug["name"], label=drug["mechanism"])

# Define layout
pos = nx.multipartite_layout(G, subset_key="subset")

# Draw the graph
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))  # High-resolution size
node_sizes = [G.nodes[node]["size"] for node in G.nodes]
node_colors = [G.nodes[node]["color"] for node in G.nodes]
nx.draw(
    G, pos, with_labels=True, node_size=node_sizes, node_color=node_colors,
    font_size=10, font_weight="bold", edge_color="gray"
)

# Add edge labels (toggle on/off for cleaner visuals)
show_labels = True
if show_labels:
    edge_labels = nx.get_edge_attributes(G, 'label')
    nx.draw_networkx_edge_labels(G, pos, edge_labels=edge_labels, font_size=8)

# Add legend
legend_elements = [
    Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', label=cat, markersize=10, markerfacecolor=color)
    for cat, color in categories.items()
]
plt.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc="upper left", fontsize=12, title="Categories")

# Save the figure
plt.title("Senotherapeutics Classification Pathway Diagram", fontsize=24)
plt.savefig("Senotherapeutics_FullDiagram.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()
